      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: bound gateway session memory after compaction",
        "body": "## Summary\n- bound Pi SessionManager in-memory transcript retention in OpenClaw runtime after compaction\n- route embedded runner, CLI runner, and CLI compaction SessionManager usage through the bounded OpenClaw wrapper\n- keep full JSONL transcript persistence intact while pruning stale pre-compaction entries from live memory\n- preserve clearer same-process port diagnostics\n\n## Why\nCurrent `main` uses `@earendil-works/pi-coding-agent@0.74.0`, whose `SessionManager` keeps every `fileEntries` entry and `byId` entry resident in live memory for long-running gateway sessions. For Paperclip/OpenClaw gateway runs, old pre-compaction transcript branches can stay resident and push gateway memory upward over time.\n\nThis PR avoids a pnpm package patch. Instead, OpenClaw installs an idempotent runtime wrapper around Pi `SessionManager` and uses it from the gateway/CLI runtime paths that open active session managers. The wrapper keeps the active branch from the latest compaction boundary forward, preserves latest state/custom metadata and retained labels, rebuilds indexes, and leaves the append-only JSONL file untouched on disk.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n**Behavior or issue addressed:** Long-running OpenClaw gateway/Paperclip sessions can keep stale pre-compaction Pi `SessionManager.fileEntries` and `byId` entries resident in memory. This branch prunes stale pre-compaction live memory through OpenClaw's bounded SessionManager wrapper while preserving the retained branch, compaction summary, current state/custom metadata, labels, and full persisted JSONL transcript.\n\n**Real environment tested:** Local OpenClaw checkout on macOS at PR head `0dc0ab3173fb6940617d4fbce2e769b0b5b2388b`, using the branch's OpenClaw wrapper import `./src/agents/pi-session-manager-memory-bound.ts` over published `@earendil-works/pi-coding-agent@0.74.0`. The proof used real persisted JSONL session storage under a temporary session directory. `PI_SESSION_MANAGER_MAX_IN_MEMORY_ENTRIES=256` was set to make the retention behavior observable in a short live run.\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch:** Ran `node --import tsx --input-type=module --eval '...'` from the OpenClaw worktree. The command imported `SessionManager` from `./src/agents/pi-session-manager-memory-bound.ts`, created a real persisted session directory, appended 300 pre-compaction message entries, appended thinking/model/session/custom state, appended a compaction entry with a retained boundary, appended post-compaction tail messages, then inspected live manager entries, resolved context, retained labels, and the persisted JSONL transcript.\n\n**Evidence after fix:** Terminal output from that live command:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"proof\": \"OPENCLAW_REAL_BEHAVIOR_PROOF\",\n  \"branchHead\": \"0dc0ab3173fb6940617d4fbce2e769b0b5b2388b\",\n  \"importPath\": \"./src/agents/pi-session-manager-memory-bound.ts\",\n  \"piPackage\": \"@earendil-works/pi-coding-agent@0.74.0\",\n  \"maxInMemoryEntries\": \"256\",\n  \"entriesBeforeCompaction\": 300,\n  \"entriesAfterCompactionInMemory\": 48,\n  \"persistedJsonlLines\": 349,\n  \"staleEntryInMemory\": false,\n  \"thinkingEntryInMemory\": true,\n  \"modelEntryInMemory\": true,\n  \"sessionInfoEntryInMemory\": true,\n  \"customEntryInMemory\": true,\n  \"firstKeptEntryInMemory\": true,\n  \"compactionEntryInMemory\": true,\n  \"keptLabel\": \"kept marker\",\n  \"sessionName\": \"Memory leak proof\",\n  \"contextThinkingLevel\": \"high\",\n  \"contextHasSummary\": true,\n  \"contextHasKeptUser\": true,\n  \"contextHasTail\": true,\n  \"contextHasStaleRawMessage\": false,\n  \"persistedTranscriptHasStaleRawMessage\": true,\n  \"persistedTranscriptHasTail\": true\n}\n```\n\n**Observed result after fix:** The stale raw pre-compaction entry was removed from live memory and no longer appeared in the built session context. The first retained entry, compaction entry, current thinking/model/session/custom metadata, retained label, compaction summary, and post-compaction tail stayed available. The persisted JSONL transcript still contained both the stale historical raw message and the post-compaction tail, so disk history was preserved while live memory was bounded.\n\n**What was not tested:** No full gateway soak test was run on this exact PR head. The live proof directly exercises the exact OpenClaw runtime wrapper now used by the embedded runner, CLI runner, and CLI compaction paths, and automated tests cover the regression path and port diagnostics.\n\n## Tests\n- `node scripts/test-projects.mjs src/agents/pi-session-manager-memory.test.ts src/infra/ports.test.ts`\n- `pnpm tsgo:prod`\n- `pnpm lint`\n- `pnpm deps:patches:check`\n- `git diff --check && node scripts/check-no-conflict-markers.mjs`\n",
        "branch": "fix/gateway-leak-triad-73655",
